        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The first thing you typically see when confronted with the long arm of the law is the cop cars swarming around you like a pack of wolves. Once, the infamous Dodge Charger pursuit halted criminals and amazed pedestrians, but there was a huge problem. The Chargers used by cops are either heavy 5.7-liter V8 or low-power V6s, making it difficult for anyone with a basic knowledge of cars to be afraid to run. Of course, those vehicles have the advantage of AWD, but there's another all-American performance car whose reputation is quite vibrant within cop culture. That car is the Ford Mustang.",
            "type": "text",
