      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Ford Mustang was once one of the most feared police chasers around in the '80s and '90s but was eventually discontinued for use by law enforcement. Nowadays, Steeda has introduced a new Mustang deemed the Special Services Mustang for the Valdosta Police department. Along with the V8 engine, the cops have been given a bright white and blue livery, suspension upgrades, a tune, and a cold air intake. This all translates to a great performance car and the perfect vehicle to help the police reclaim their image of skill, honor, and general toughness in the face of adversity.",
